Reasoning: The paper deals with regular sets and their properties, which are typically studied in the field of formal languages (cs.FL). The concepts of almost-confluent congruential languages (ACCL) and Church-Rosser congruential languages (CRCL) are related to rewriting systems, which fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to construct examples of ACCLs that are not CRCLs. Finally, information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant in analyzing the properties of these languages.
